# Environment Variables Reference

This file lists all required environment variables for running the DRCCS backend services, both locally (Docker Compose) and in AWS (ECS/EKS).

---

## Common Variables
- `SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE` — Spring Boot profile (e.g., `prod`)
- `SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL` — JDBC URL for PostgreSQL
- `SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME` — Database username
- `SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD` — Database password
- `SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO` — Hibernate DDL mode
- `SPRING_JPA_PROPERTIES_HIBERNATE_DIALECT` — Hibernate dialect

## Service Discovery
- `EUREKA_CLIENT_SERVICEURL_DEFAULTZONE` — Eureka server URL
- `EUREKA_INSTANCE_PREFER_IP_ADDRESS` — Prefer IP address for Eureka registration
- `EUREKA_INSTANCE_HOSTNAME` — Service hostname for Eureka

## Kafka (for incident/notification services)
- `SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS` — Kafka broker address

## Database Container
- `POSTGRES_USER` — PostgreSQL username
- `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` — PostgreSQL password
- `POSTGRES_DB` — Default database name

## Notification Service
- `SPRING_APPLICATION_NAME` — Service name
- `SERVER_PORT` — Service port

---

## Usage
- Set these variables in your Docker Compose file for local development.
- For AWS deployments, set these in ECS task definitions or use AWS Secrets Manager/SSM Parameter Store for sensitive values.

---

## Example (.env.example)
```
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod
SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://<db-host>:5432/<db-name>
SPRING_DATASOURCE_USERNAME=postgres
SPRING_DATASOURCE_PASSWORD=yourpassword
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=update
SPRING_JPA_PROPERTIES_HIBERNATE_DIALECT=org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect
EUREKA_CLIENT_SERVICEURL_DEFAULTZONE=http://<eureka-host>:8761/eureka/
EUREKA_INSTANCE_PREFER_IP_ADDRESS=true
EUREKA_INSTANCE_HOSTNAME=your-service
SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=<kafka-host>:9092
POSTGRES_USER=postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=yourpassword
POSTGRES_DB=postgres
SPRING_APPLICATION_NAME=notification-service
SERVER_PORT=8085
```

---

Document and update this file as new variables are added or changed.
